# agents.slice — user-scope memory ceiling for interactive agent CLI processes
# (claude/codex/cursor/gemini/etc) AND any orchestration that spawns them
# (ao-daemon). Part of bead ez-gh-actions-0725 (panel decision recorded on
# ez-gh-actions-ah94, Tier 1 do-now item #2; round-3 policy flip on
# 2026-07-12 from opt-in to AUTO-MIGRATE-with-OPT-OUT).
#
# HOW A PROCESS JOINS THIS SLICE (round-3 policy: AUTO-MIGRATE, --opt-out):
#   Default behavior is AUTO-MIGRATE — every interactive agent CLI process
#   and any ao-daemon.service descendant discovered on the host MUST be
#   enrolled in agents.slice by default. The script that enforces this is
#   scripts/host/agent-auto-migrate.sh (added in lane G of round 3):
#
#     scripts/host/agent-auto-migrate.sh apply     # relaunch matching PIDs
#     scripts/host/agent-auto-migrate.sh apply --dry-run
#     scripts/host/agent-auto-migrate.sh status    # enrolled leaves + RSS
#
#   The auto-migrate helper discovers already-running PIDs by base name
#   (claude, codex, gemini, cursor, aider, cody), captures their argv +
#   cwd, SIGTERMs the original, and relaunches via
#   `systemd-run --user --slice=agents.slice --scope -- <cmd>` (so the
#   relaunched process inherits this slice's MemoryHigh=20G). Cgroup v2
#   cannot move a running process into a new slice mid-flight without
#   sub-tree privileges, so the relaunch pathway is the only supported
#   mechanism — see agent-auto-migrate.sh header for the full rationale.
#
#   For NEW sessions, the legacy opt-in wrapper still exists at
#   scripts/host/agent-cli-scoped.sh (gained a `--auto-attach` flag in
#   round 3 that uses the same systemd-run pathway as auto-migrate). Use
#   it when you want a NEW session to start inside the slice from the
#   outset without going through the migrate-then-relaunch dance.
#
#   The OPT-OUT escape hatch is a single env-var on the running session:
#     AGENT_SLICE_OPT_OUT=1 scripts/host/agent-cli-scoped.sh <command>
#   When set, agent-cli-scoped.sh runs the command unscoped (no
#   `--slice=agents.slice`); otherwise it inherits the auto-attach path
#   and the new session joins the slice. A user-scope drop-in for
#   ao-daemon.service lives at
#   systemd/ao-daemon-memory-cap.service.d/memory.conf and enforces the
#   same slice enrollment on the daemon without any per-session flag.
#
#   This unit only needs to exist under ~/.config/systemd/user/ for any
#   of the above to work — systemd auto-starts a slice the first time a
#   scope/service references it. No `systemctl --user enable` step is
#   required or performed by this repo's install path; see install.sh
#   comments near the auxiliary unit loop for why this unit is
#   intentionally NOT swept into the `ezgha-*.service`/`ezgha-*.timer`
#   glob (it is a host-wide concern, not ezgha-fleet-specific, and stays
#   auto-migrated by script rather than by an ezgha-systemd-unit install
#   hook — this lets the install path stay one-writer and avoids the
#   2026-07-07 install-loop race).
#
# AUTO-MIGRATION TRIGGER (how the helper runs by default):
#   The auto-migrate helper is invoked BY a one-shot systemd user service
#   that runs on user-session-start (recommended path) AND by the
#   verify-exit-criteria.sh Gate 8 (2) probe (fails-closed if any
#   agent-CLI binary on PATH has zero enrolled leaves in this slice).
#   Wiring the service is out of scope for this slice file — see
#   scripts/host/install.sh and bead ez-gh-actions-0725 followups for
#   the systemd path unit that the harness owns. Until that ships,
#   operators run `scripts/host/agent-auto-migrate.sh apply` manually on
#   session start; the policy change here is "default-on" rather than
#   "default-auto-on-boot," pending the systemd path unit.
#
# WHY MemoryHigh (not MemoryMax): MemoryHigh is a *soft* ceiling — the
# kernel throttles the cgroup and aggressively reclaims its reclaimable
# memory (page cache first, then swaps out anonymous pages) once usage
# exceeds the threshold, but it does NOT invoke the OOM killer against
# member processes. That is the deliberate choice here: a safety mechanism
# must not itself cause the outage it's meant to prevent (repo CLAUDE.md
# "Self-Outage Prevention Principle") — a hard MemoryMax on a live coding
# agent's cgroup would SIGKILL agents outright, turning a memory-pressure
# warning into forced session loss, which is worse than the degrade-and-
# slow-down behavior MemoryHigh gives you.
#
# BLAST RADIUS / NORMAL PEAK / SAFE MARGIN (required by repo CLAUDE.md
# "Safety & Monitoring Principles" for any new threshold):
#   - Normal peak observed (2026-07-08 through 2026-07-10 incident window):
#     host squeezed to ~14GB of headroom outside the Colima VM (which holds
#     a static 48GiB/24cpu allocation of the 62GB host total, out of scope
#     for this bead) across ~25-29 concurrent claude/codex/agent CLI
#     processes plus the ezgha daemon and system processes. That ~14GB
#     window is what pegged the 16GB swapfile at 99-100% utilization for
#     multiple days, produced D-state process pileup, and spiked load
#     average to 218, triggering a watchdog reboot on 2026-07-10 that
#     killed an in-progress agent session.
#   - MemoryHigh=20G leaves roughly 6GB of throttling headroom above that
#     observed ~14GB peak before this slice starts reclaiming/throttling
#     its own member processes. It is deliberately NOT set at or below the
#     observed peak — the goal is to catch runaway growth *beyond* what has
#     already been observed as "normal but uncomfortable," not to throttle
#     the fleet's steady-state operation and cause a second, self-inflicted
#     degradation.
#   - This ceiling applies ONLY to processes explicitly launched via
#     agent-cli-scoped.sh into this slice — it has zero effect on the
#     ezgha daemon, the Colima VM, or any process not opted in.
#
# Static syntax validation only (no live start/enable performed by this
# commit): `systemd-analyze verify systemd/agents.slice`

[Unit]
Description=Interactive agent CLI processes (claude/codex/cursor/etc) — soft memory ceiling
Before=slices.target

[Slice]
MemoryHigh=20G
MemoryAccounting=yes
